To find ip of both use "ip a" command
on kali: use the ip [Kali_ip]

On ubuntu use the same command to find ubuntu ip [Ubuntu_ip]
On Kali teminal run the 
"nmap -A [Ubuntu_ip]" command
if this doesnt work use -Pn
This will
nmap: The command to run Nmap.
-A: Enables OS detection, version detection, script scanning, and traceroute.
[Ubuntu_ip]: The IP address of the target machine you want to scan
use -Pn if not working
